ution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Boyce   and   Boyes  .","Probably also an Americanized form of French   Bois  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Boyce","meanings":["English and Irish (mainly Donegal): of Norman origin, a habitational name from from one or more places in Normandy named with Old French <i>bois</i> ‘wood, grove’, especially Bois-Arnault and Bus-Saint-Rémy (Eure), and Bosc-le-Hard (Seine-Maritime), each of which is known to have given its name to an aristocratic Norman family in England. The name was taken by the Normans from England to Ireland, where it was also adopted to Anglicize Irish <b>Ó Buadhaigh</b> (see   Bogue  ).","English: variant of   Bush  , influenced by Old French <i>bois</i> in 1 above, or else a translation of this term.","Americanized form of French   Bois  ."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Boys was born after 1480, in Lincolnshire, England as the daughter of Elizabeth Alday. She married John Thimbley Sr before 1507. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters. She died in 1538."},"et":{"after 1480–1538":"pärast 1480–1538","1480–1538":"1480–1538","1482–1550":"1482–1550","1507–Male":"1510–Surnud","1509–Female":"1509–Surnud","1510–1590":"1510–1590","1524–Female":"1524–Surnud","1465–Female":"1465–Surnud","after 1480":"pärast 1480","1550":"1550","before 1507":"enne 1507","1482":"1482","1590":"1590","1480":"1480","1524":"1524","1510":"1510","1465":"1465","about 1524":"umbes 1524","abt 1509":"umbes 1509","1509":"1509","1507":"1510","abt. 1507":"umbes 1507","1538":"1538","Derbyshire, England":"Derbyshire, England","Irnham, Lincoln, England":"Irnham, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","Irnham, Linc., Eng.":"Irnham, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Irnham, Lincolnshire, England":"Irnham, Lincolnshire, England"},"fi":{"after 1480–1538":"1480 jälkeen–1538","1480–1538":"1480–1538","1482–1550":"1482–1550","1507–Male":"1510–Kuollut","1509–Female":"1509–Kuollut","1510–1590":"1510–1590","1524–Female":"1524–Kuollut","1465–Female":"1465–Kuollut","after 1480":"1480 jälkeen","1550":"1550","before 1507":"ennen vuotta 1507","1482":"1482","1590":"1590","1480":"1480","1524":"1524","1510":"1510","1465":"1465","about 1524":"noin 1524","abt 1509":"noin 1509","1509":"1509","1507":"1510","abt. 1507":"noin 1507","1538":"1538","Derbyshire, England":"Derbyshire, England","Irnham, Lincoln, England":"Irnham, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","Irnham, Linc., Eng.":"Irnham, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta",